Royal Mail Group Plans to Cut 40,000 Jobs, Sunday Times Says

-- B y   E m m a   C h a r l t o n
-- 
2011-06-05T06:33:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-05/royal-mail-group-plans-to-cut-40-000-jobs-sunday-times-says.html
Royal Mail  Group Ltd. plans to cut
40,000 jobs in the next five years, the  Sunday Times  reported,
citing a business plan prepared by Chief Executive Officer Moya Greene.  Greene is close to agreeing to the plan with the U.K.
government before Royal Mail tries to attract buyers next year,
the newspaper reported. The cuts are equivalent to one-quarter
of the workforce, according to the Sunday Times.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Emma Charlton in London at 
 echarlton1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dick Schumacher at 
 dschumacher@bloomberg.net  